WEBVTT

00:07.925 --> 00:09.836
You better run!

00:10.010 --> 00:13.173
It’s like pouring boiling water
on fire ants! Whoo!

00:14.097 --> 00:17.464
Hear me, slaves. Kill the king.

00:17.643 --> 00:18.678
[GRUNTS]

00:19.228 --> 00:20.593
[PEOPLE SCREAMING]

00:20.771 --> 00:22.386
[MARNIE SPEAKING IN LATIN]

00:25.609 --> 00:27.099
[GRUNTING]

00:27.277 --> 00:29.142
Get the fuck out of here!

00:35.118 --> 00:36.983
Eric!

00:39.706 --> 00:41.162
[SPEAKING IN LATIN]

00:41.333 --> 00:43.369
Must kill the king.

00:43.961 --> 00:46.418
-Here comes death.
-Let him go!

00:47.297 --> 00:48.878
Not for me.

00:49.299 --> 00:50.630
[SCREAMS]

00:51.343 --> 00:53.208
[GUNSHOTS]

00:53.428 --> 00:55.168
[BOTH SPEAKING IN LATIN]

00:55.597 --> 00:57.007
[GROWLING]

00:57.558 --> 00:59.219
[SCREAMS]

00:59.393 --> 01:02.226
-Silver.
SOOKIE: Bill, please don’t.

01:02.729 --> 01:04.469
[GROANS]

01:04.731 --> 01:06.562
Don’t let her control you. Fight her.

01:06.733 --> 01:09.019
Go home.

01:09.778 --> 01:11.814
[GRUNTING]

01:16.743 --> 01:17.949
SooMe,go!

01:23.500 --> 01:26.333
-What the fuck?
-Broken.

03:14.653 --> 03:17.611
What have I done?

03:18.323 --> 03:19.824
[GROANING]

03:19.991 --> 03:22.027
MAN:
Oh, no.

03:22.202 --> 03:24.944
GIRL:
Mama, wake up.

03:25.122 --> 03:27.829
Mama, please wake up.

03:27.999 --> 03:32.663
Mama, please wake up, Mama!

03:34.464 --> 03:35.499
Bill!

03:36.675 --> 03:39.792
-I think he might be--
-Get off me.

03:44.141 --> 03:45.802
Marnie.

03:46.893 --> 03:48.599
[SPEAKS IN LATIN]

03:52.733 --> 03:55.315
NAN:
We have to help these poor people.

03:55.485 --> 03:57.567
Bill, image.

03:58.655 --> 04:00.361
Everybody stay calm.

04:00.532 --> 04:03.148
The fire department
and EMTs are on the way.

04:03.326 --> 04:07.660
I myself am a trained, caring
and certified first responder.

04:21.511 --> 04:23.376
We didn’t do anything wrong.

04:25.515 --> 04:27.176
You sure?

04:28.226 --> 04:30.012
I’m a free woman.

04:31.521 --> 04:35.389
Hoyt broke up with me,
and I broke up with him.

04:35.567 --> 04:37.523
Well, I didn’t.

04:38.195 --> 04:40.186
Well, listen to you.

04:40.363 --> 04:42.024
God.

04:42.532 --> 04:44.818
Talk about bromance.

04:45.118 --> 04:47.655
Well, he is my brother.

04:49.331 --> 04:52.323
He was the littlest one
in elementary school...

04:52.501 --> 04:56.540
...if I didn’t do his fighting for him, those
other kids would like to have killed him.

04:56.713 --> 04:58.249
I know.

04:58.423 --> 05:01.506
You’ve told me and Hoyt’s told me
many, many times.

05:01.676 --> 05:04.634
In 8th grade, he shot up ten inches.

05:04.805 --> 05:07.467
No muscle yet, no balance at all.

05:07.641 --> 05:10.257
That boy had to walk
with a cane for six months.

05:10.435 --> 05:12.767
Somebody had to help him then too,
and that was me.

05:12.938 --> 05:15.099
Well, Hoyt walks just fine
all on his own now.

05:15.273 --> 05:17.184
Maybe it’s time you let him.

05:18.693 --> 05:21.685
-You’re as bad as Maxine.
-Yeah, maybe you’re right.

05:23.573 --> 05:26.235
Hey, Jess, you and me....

05:27.410 --> 05:30.243
This is different. This will kill him.

05:32.165 --> 05:35.749
-Look, I don’t want to hurt him either.
-It was the blood, ain't it?

05:36.962 --> 05:39.749
I never would have done it
if I hadn’t have drank your blood.

05:39.923 --> 05:42.005
Bullshit.

05:42.676 --> 05:46.168
Don’t you dare pretend
that you didn’t want me.

05:49.516 --> 05:53.179
But I’ll never be able
to face him again unless you....

05:59.234 --> 06:03.273
You want to wipe everything that happened
between us tonight right out of your mind?

06:04.614 --> 06:06.605
You have any idea
how that makes me feel?

06:06.783 --> 06:09.365
Well, |-- I don’t know what else to do.

06:09.536 --> 06:11.276
This is for you too.

06:11.454 --> 06:13.661
He’ll know about us
as soon as he looks at me.

06:14.124 --> 06:18.367
I am not gonna glamour you
just because you don’t want to feel guilty.

06:18.545 --> 06:22.129
What about my guilt?
Who’s gonna make me forget?

06:24.426 --> 06:27.133
Fucking humans.

06:28.805 --> 06:30.887
I’m gonna go find somebody to eat.

06:37.314 --> 06:39.475
Hang on.
We’ll be at the hospital in five minutes.

06:39.649 --> 06:40.809
[GROANS]

06:40.984 --> 06:44.977
A few stitches, little duct tape,
pretty nurse, you’ll be good to go.

06:45.155 --> 06:48.022
-They can’t do nothing for me.
-Quit talking shit.

06:48.199 --> 06:50.190
It ain't just the beating.

06:50.368 --> 06:55.032
Turning into Sam, it did something.

06:57.125 --> 06:59.286
Shifter to werewolf.

07:00.795 --> 07:02.660
I’m dying.

07:03.298 --> 07:05.084
We gotta try.

07:05.300 --> 07:07.086
[GROANING]

07:09.512 --> 07:11.764
Jesus, fuck!

07:14.100 --> 07:16.011
Take me home.

07:17.020 --> 07:18.510
Please.

07:20.982 --> 07:22.392
Where’s home?

07:25.779 --> 07:27.189
Merlotte’s.

07:33.787 --> 07:35.903
-Hey, how many bars do you have?
CASEY: Four.

07:36.081 --> 07:38.823
No, two again. One.

07:39.000 --> 07:42.709
I don’t have any bars anywhere ever.
My phone sucks. Ow!

07:42.879 --> 07:48.215
People, we are locked the fuck up
and incommunicado.

07:48.385 --> 07:51.593
-Faceit
-Magic is not stronger than technology.

07:51.763 --> 07:55.551
CASEY: Three. Wait, no, one again.
TREVOR: Damn.

07:55.725 --> 07:57.761
Ma, hello? Hello? Mom.

07:57.936 --> 08:01.474
I am not gonna die in a Wiccan shit store
with them. I fucking refuse.

08:01.648 --> 08:05.061
There ain't no spell that can’t be undone
if you got the juice.

08:05.235 --> 08:07.942
Marnie, or Antonia,
it’s just another witch.

08:08.113 --> 08:10.229
I’m not the fucking ancient,
pissed-off witch.

08:10.407 --> 08:12.739
She ain't no more pissed off than I am.

08:12.909 --> 08:15.150
-You?
-Yeah. I got some rage.

08:16.955 --> 08:20.163
We are strong, angry women, Tara.

08:20.333 --> 08:23.040
All we gotta do is force a crack
in her wall.

08:23.211 --> 08:25.076
There’s an incantation here.

08:25.255 --> 08:26.495
[SCREAMS]

08:26.840 --> 08:30.128
You should have been there.
It was a bloodbath, and we sort of won.

08:30.301 --> 08:32.257
Enough, Roy.

08:32.929 --> 08:34.885
CASEY: Come on.
-Put the vampires inside.

08:35.056 --> 08:36.341
Come on, robots.

08:36.516 --> 08:38.507
TREVOR: Where’s the other one?
Where’s the tall one?

08:38.852 --> 08:40.342
CASEY:
Who are they?

08:41.271 --> 08:44.229
-ls, uh, anything wrong?
-Yes.

08:44.399 --> 08:47.266
No, no. Yes.

08:47.694 --> 08:49.810
What’s Roy mean? What bloodbath?

08:49.988 --> 08:51.569
You can’t hold us prisoner.

08:53.742 --> 08:57.576
Why are you all so ungrateful?

08:58.788 --> 09:02.451
I am protecting you.

09:03.960 --> 09:09.455
l have put my soul at risk
to destroy the night beasts for you.

09:11.843 --> 09:13.379
But at what cost?

09:13.553 --> 09:17.045
We won’t say anything to anybody,
we promise.

09:17.807 --> 09:21.391
MARNIE:
We will all stay together.

09:21.561 --> 09:23.802
[MARNIE MUTTERING INDISTINCTLY]

09:23.980 --> 09:26.312
| see it. Well, I don't see it.

09:26.483 --> 09:28.519
[MUTTERING INDISTINCTLY]

09:33.198 --> 09:35.610
You’ve been keeping secrets from me.

09:35.909 --> 09:38.696
What’s the deal with your dairy maid
and her lightning trick?

09:38.870 --> 09:41.532
We have more important concerns.

09:41.706 --> 09:43.947
There are glamour squads
all over Shreveport.

09:44.125 --> 09:46.832
If anything leaks,
remember the civil rights movement...

09:47.003 --> 09:50.040
...sweeping social change
inevitably accompanied by violence...

09:50.215 --> 09:52.706
...and the appearance of chaos,
yada yada.

09:53.384 --> 09:54.840
That is the spin we’ll give it.

09:55.011 --> 09:57.172
-Spin doesn’t matter now.
-Spin always matters.

09:57.347 --> 10:00.510
You are not in charge anymore.

10:02.227 --> 10:05.264
Oh, yes. Yes, lam.

10:05.438 --> 10:10.023
I raised you to that throne,
and I can bring you down in a heartbeat.

10:11.528 --> 10:14.110
This is your fault, all of it.

10:14.280 --> 10:16.896
And that is exactly
what I’m gonna tell the Authority.

10:17.075 --> 10:20.192
-What are you talking about?
-If you’d let me kill that witch--

10:20.370 --> 10:22.952
If you had any idea of the factions
I’m fighting with--

10:23.123 --> 10:26.707
I don’t care.
Now, this is what will happen.

10:26.876 --> 10:30.334
We are going after the necromancer
and we are taking her out.

10:30.505 --> 10:32.541
By any means necessary.

10:35.051 --> 10:37.463
I remember everything.

10:38.513 --> 10:40.049
Us.

10:41.391 --> 10:43.552
Nothing’s changed.

10:43.726 --> 10:44.932
Except you.

10:45.103 --> 10:46.684
I haven’t changed.

10:47.856 --> 10:50.563
I’m just more.

10:51.943 --> 10:54.150
The other Eric is still here.

10:54.487 --> 10:57.069
-Uh-huh.
-SooMe.

11:02.162 --> 11:03.698
Look at me.

11:07.083 --> 11:09.290
Can’t you see him in my eyes?

11:15.008 --> 11:16.589
Yes.

11:17.594 --> 11:18.834
So, what’s the problem?

11:22.098 --> 11:23.554
BiII.

11:26.352 --> 11:28.729
When you were about to kill him...

11:29.564 --> 11:33.603
...| just couldn’t bear the thought
of a world without him in it.

11:34.444 --> 11:37.277
I think it was how I was able to stop you.

11:40.909 --> 11:42.399
I love you.

11:44.495 --> 11:46.872
I don’t want to lie to you...

11:47.790 --> 11:49.496
...but I can’t help it.

11:49.667 --> 11:53.330
-I love him too.
-How is that possible?

11:54.464 --> 11:59.834
Sometimes I think it’s because
you’ve both given me your blood.

12:01.304 --> 12:04.467
Maybe it’s just chemical.

12:04.641 --> 12:09.135
You gave yourself to me completely.

12:10.480 --> 12:14.223
-You are mine.
-I never promised that.

12:21.241 --> 12:22.981
Yes, I did.

12:25.370 --> 12:27.156
I love you.

12:32.335 --> 12:35.919
Bill called me. Are you back? Is it you?

12:36.089 --> 12:38.000
Yes, I’m back.

12:38.383 --> 12:39.919
My God, I missed you.

12:41.177 --> 12:44.340
That fucking sorceress,
I thought I’d lost you forever.

12:44.973 --> 12:46.804
How did you get her to break the curse?

12:46.975 --> 12:48.340
Well, she didn’t.

12:48.518 --> 12:50.349
Sookie did.

12:51.145 --> 12:52.430
Oh.

12:55.942 --> 12:59.025
-Well, thanks.
-Don’t mention it.

12:59.445 --> 13:02.653
Why didn’t you summon me
the second you were free?

13:06.160 --> 13:07.411
Hey.

13:10.164 --> 13:12.029
We’ll talk about it later.

13:13.626 --> 13:15.036
Sure.

13:17.297 --> 13:18.787
Fine.

13:23.052 --> 13:26.340
Fire killed her 400 years ago.
We can only hope that it works again.

13:26.514 --> 13:29.426
Blowing up Moongoddess Emporium
is not a 21st century solution.

13:29.600 --> 13:32.933
-Blowing up Moongoddess?
-You’re fucking our agenda up the ass.

13:33.104 --> 13:34.890
Get me off
the Greta Van Susteren show.

13:35.064 --> 13:37.806
-God, I hate her.
-Bil|, you can’t do this.

13:37.984 --> 13:41.522
-Tara and other humans are in there.
ERIC: Well, they bet on the wrong horse.

13:41.696 --> 13:44.403
-lt’s too bad.
BILL: I’ve summoned Jessica.

13:44.574 --> 13:47.361
We’ll secure the windows,
silver ourselves and go to ground.

13:47.535 --> 13:49.116
-Pam, you’ll stay here.
-l’m so in.

13:49.287 --> 13:51.323
If Tara hadn’t warned me
about the hotel...

13:51.497 --> 13:53.613
...Eric would be a zombie
and you'd be dead.

13:53.791 --> 13:56.077
My kind is still in danger.

13:56.252 --> 13:59.995
I can’t risk potential genocide to save
one human just because she’s your friend.

14:00.173 --> 14:02.459
Lovable, isn’t he?

14:02.967 --> 14:04.298
At least let me help. I can--

14:04.469 --> 14:07.632
Last time you helped,
you got shot and almost died.

14:10.099 --> 14:11.839
Stay away from there, Sookie.

14:12.018 --> 14:14.600
Tomorrow we’re gonna finish Marnie
once and for all.

14:14.771 --> 14:17.854
-And if innocent people die?
-lt’s war. It happens.

14:23.071 --> 14:24.106
[DOOR CLOSES]

14:35.166 --> 14:36.622
No.

14:36.793 --> 14:40.160
-No.
-Sam.

14:41.547 --> 14:42.878
[GROANS]

14:43.049 --> 14:44.459
Okay.

14:44.634 --> 14:46.795
We gotta-- We gotta get him
some vampire blood.

14:46.969 --> 14:49.301
No. No.

14:49.806 --> 14:51.296
No.

14:51.933 --> 14:54.265
He’s got a right to choose his time.

15:01.109 --> 15:02.224
Okay.

15:03.236 --> 15:05.318
Okay, okay.

15:11.035 --> 15:12.991
Can’t hardly feel nothing now.

15:13.162 --> 15:14.902
Hey, hey.

15:15.540 --> 15:16.905
You fool kid.

15:23.589 --> 15:24.965
Nice.

15:26.426 --> 15:29.008
SAM: Well.
-lt’s company.

15:32.557 --> 15:34.422
Don’t be afraid.

15:43.359 --> 15:45.350
You know, I’m--

15:46.487 --> 15:51.356
I’m thinking the folks who pass on
for a little while and then come back....

15:52.994 --> 15:55.906
Well, they say it’s beautiful over there.

15:56.914 --> 15:58.950
There’s books on it.

15:59.125 --> 16:02.743
They all want to stay.
They say it’s like going home.

16:04.338 --> 16:05.748
Yeah.

16:06.674 --> 16:12.385
It’s all feeling good,
and white light, and people who love you.

16:13.222 --> 16:15.213
You really believe that shit?

16:17.602 --> 16:20.719
-Why not?
-Now, could be.

16:22.565 --> 16:24.897
There ain't no heaven...

16:26.402 --> 16:29.109
...and hell’s a dogfight.

16:30.615 --> 16:34.073
I’m gonna disappear like I never was.

16:35.244 --> 16:37.075
That’s what I want.

16:38.664 --> 16:44.330
Well, won’t you be surprised
when angels come and lift you up.

16:47.632 --> 16:49.588
Sucker.

16:56.182 --> 16:57.797
Hey.

17:04.065 --> 17:06.306
I’m sorry, Sam.

17:07.860 --> 17:09.270
For everything.

17:09.612 --> 17:11.102
No.

17:11.864 --> 17:14.241
No, nothing was your fault.

17:15.493 --> 17:19.532
And listen, I’m sorry.
I should have been a better brother. |--

17:19.705 --> 17:20.956
I didn’t know how.

17:23.876 --> 17:26.458
You were the best part of my life.

17:33.553 --> 17:35.714
That is so fucking sad.

17:35.888 --> 17:36.923
[SNIFFLING]

17:39.809 --> 17:42.300
Sam, he’s going.

17:43.688 --> 17:46.350
Don’t forget me right away.

17:46.524 --> 17:47.889
Tommy.

17:48.067 --> 17:50.934
Tommy, I’ll never forget about you.

17:51.487 --> 17:54.820
You’re in my heart, always.

17:55.491 --> 17:56.992
You’re my brother.

18:01.163 --> 18:02.994
Tommy.

18:03.165 --> 18:04.450
Hey.

18:04.625 --> 18:08.334
Tommy, listen. You’re loved. I love you.

18:15.428 --> 18:17.419
Oh, God.

18:23.769 --> 18:25.350
[SNIFFLES]

18:41.287 --> 18:44.779
Marcus Bozeman is a dead fucking wolf.

18:50.504 --> 18:52.415
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

18:53.549 --> 18:55.756
[JASON SIGHS]

19:05.394 --> 19:07.350
You ain't gonna let me in?

19:07.980 --> 19:10.562
Oh, well, place is kind Of a mess. Heh.

19:10.733 --> 19:12.394
I don’t give a shit.

19:18.741 --> 19:19.981
What’s on?

19:20.159 --> 19:22.320
I don’t know. Something.

19:22.912 --> 19:24.152
Well, who’s playing?

19:24.330 --> 19:26.537
lt’s them against them. Heh.

19:30.878 --> 19:31.913
Want a beer?

19:32.088 --> 19:35.421
Uh, I had a beer for breakfast,
so, what else you got?

19:35.633 --> 19:37.624
Uh....

19:37.802 --> 19:39.463
Well, nothing.

19:39.637 --> 19:41.298
Just beer.

19:41.972 --> 19:44.349
I guess I’ll have a beer then.

19:46.143 --> 19:47.474
Okay.

20:00.449 --> 20:01.780
You know, that house is, uh....

20:01.951 --> 20:03.782
It’s pretty empty.

20:06.497 --> 20:10.115
It’s like too full, too empty,
all at once, you know?

20:10.292 --> 20:11.702
Yeah.

20:11.877 --> 20:14.459
Keep thinking I see her turning the corner.

20:14.630 --> 20:18.043
Or I’ll get a whiff of perfume
from the pillow.

20:18.217 --> 20:21.630
You know, I washed it a bunch of times,
but I can still smell her.

20:22.388 --> 20:25.972
Smells, boy....

20:26.934 --> 20:29.767
They’ll take you right back in time,
won’t they?

20:31.981 --> 20:34.814
And she’s gone for good. Thank God.

20:34.984 --> 20:38.442
You know, I’m a lucky man
to be out of that mess.

20:39.363 --> 20:40.978
Yeah.

20:41.490 --> 20:44.072
I can’t stay at that place, J.

20:44.410 --> 20:46.571
Like, I don’t want her back.

20:49.165 --> 20:51.656
But I keep waiting to see her
walk through the door...

20:51.834 --> 20:55.326
...like crawl up out of her cubby hole,
you know, and....

20:55.504 --> 20:58.416
All kind of cute and kind Of sleepy,
you know?

20:58.841 --> 21:00.047
Don’t.

21:00.217 --> 21:02.503
Hey, don’t do this to yourself.

21:04.847 --> 21:06.678
I’m cool.

21:07.349 --> 21:08.850
I’m great.

21:11.228 --> 21:14.015
Just let me crash with you
for a little while, will you?

21:16.859 --> 21:18.144
Yeah.

21:18.319 --> 21:21.061
Sure. NO problem.

21:22.656 --> 21:24.317
[HOYT SNIFFLING]

21:25.701 --> 21:26.986
Bubba.

21:29.246 --> 21:30.656
Hey, don’t cry, man.

21:30.831 --> 21:32.662
I ain't crying.

21:32.917 --> 21:35.033
[HOYT SNIFFLING]

21:37.338 --> 21:39.624
TERRY:
Open your eyes, mister.

21:39.799 --> 21:42.757
-Huh?
-V? Seriously, V?

21:42.927 --> 21:44.258
Oh, no.

21:44.428 --> 21:47.295
Wait a minute. Hey, uh.... Well--

21:47.473 --> 21:50.055
-lt’s not what you think, |--
-We have little children.

21:50.226 --> 21:53.093
If one of them got into that--
Oh, dear God in heaven.

21:53.270 --> 21:56.262
After everything we’ve been through,
Andy, I cannot believe you.

21:56.440 --> 21:59.978
-There’s a safety cap, I think.
-That ain't the point!

22:00.486 --> 22:02.067
Hold on.

22:02.238 --> 22:06.197
What? You think it’s mine?
No way. Come on now.

22:06.367 --> 22:07.402
lt’s evidence.

22:07.576 --> 22:09.862
Are you gonna let him sit there
and bareface lie?

22:10.037 --> 22:11.493
Hey, that’s crossing a line.

22:11.664 --> 22:13.404
Me?

22:13.582 --> 22:17.166
You are an elected official
on illegal drugs.

22:17.336 --> 22:19.952
Yeah? Well, this ain't even your house!

22:20.130 --> 22:21.415
Arlene, go back to bed.

22:21.590 --> 22:23.797
-But he-- |-- Okay.
TERRY: I got this.

22:24.969 --> 22:26.425
Okay.

22:26.929 --> 22:30.763
You ain't coming near my babies
until you get yourself straight, Andy.

22:33.769 --> 22:37.353
You got no right
to bust into my private bedroom.

22:42.820 --> 22:46.278
I wanted to catch you early and apologize
about the awful things I said...

22:46.448 --> 22:49.155
-...when we were saving Mikey.
-Fine. Leave me alone.

22:49.326 --> 22:50.987
ldon’t think so.

22:51.495 --> 22:54.487
-You and me, we got somewhere to go.
-The hell we do.

22:56.041 --> 22:58.453
-Where?
-Fort Bellefleur.

23:17.771 --> 23:19.272
Why are you looking at me funny?

23:19.440 --> 23:22.682
I’m just wondering why you don’t have
more sympathy for poor Hoyt.

23:24.320 --> 23:27.983
I got more sympathy for that boy
than anybody else in the entire world.

23:28.657 --> 23:31.524
But he’s either crying
or ranting and raving...

23:31.702 --> 23:34.739
...or telling me something he’s told me
500 times already.

23:34.914 --> 23:37.075
He won’t stop talking about Jessica.

23:37.249 --> 23:39.956
Love doesn’t leave in a second
if it goes deep.

23:40.127 --> 23:42.914
It takes a long, long time.

23:43.088 --> 23:44.624
Then he drank 11 of my beers.

23:44.798 --> 23:47.335
Passed out and started farting,
continuously.

23:47.509 --> 23:50.000
Jason, I did not need to know that.

23:50.179 --> 23:53.637
So can I stay here tonight or not?

23:53.807 --> 23:56.389
Of course. But--

23:56.560 --> 23:58.346
I need your help.

24:00.022 --> 24:02.559
If it’s got anything to do with vampires,
no, thank you.

24:02.733 --> 24:04.348
l’ll sleep in my truck.

24:04.526 --> 24:06.562
Bill wants to blow up
Moongoddess Emporium...

24:06.737 --> 24:09.069
...and Tara’s in there.

24:09.949 --> 24:12.691
Well, he can’t do that. What the fuck for?

24:13.535 --> 24:15.787
Because of what happened
at the Dorchester.

24:15.955 --> 24:17.491
What happened?

24:18.290 --> 24:19.370
[SIGHS]

24:21.251 --> 24:22.957
Fuck are we doing here?

24:23.128 --> 24:24.834
TERRY:
I’m gonna save your goddamn life.

24:25.005 --> 24:28.714
-Hanging around our old tree fort?
-Where we come when there’s trouble.

24:28.884 --> 24:30.875
When we were kids.
I ain't a kid no more.

24:31.053 --> 24:34.887
You sure? Looks like you’ve been
sucking down V like it’s mother’s milk.

24:35.057 --> 24:39.892
-Don’t you talk about my mother.
-Oh, we’re gonna talk about it all today.

24:42.064 --> 24:46.398
For a year after the Marines,
you lived up there like an insane squirrel.

24:46.902 --> 24:48.233
You checked up on me.

24:48.404 --> 24:50.770
Brought me groceries,
kept the family Off my back...

24:50.948 --> 24:53.690
...even when I thought
you was an Iraqi insurgent.

24:53.867 --> 24:56.700
-Now I’m gonna repay the favor.
-Oh, yeah.

24:56.870 --> 24:59.998
That’s while you were doing piles
Of every fucking pill they make...

25:00.165 --> 25:03.657
...not to mention smack, meth and crack.

25:03.836 --> 25:05.792
Did I bust you? Hell, no.

25:05.963 --> 25:08.329
Well, I got clean in the long run,
now, didn't I?

25:08.507 --> 25:10.668
No drugs for me,
except the anti-psychotics.

25:10.843 --> 25:14.256
Now when I need a little understanding,
you hijack me from my own home.

25:14.430 --> 25:17.593
You don't have a home, Andy,
any more than I did then.

25:17.766 --> 25:20.758
You live with Grandmama,
just like when we was kids.

25:20.936 --> 25:22.676
Fuck you.

25:22.938 --> 25:24.178
[ANDY GRUNTS]

25:25.649 --> 25:27.435
V is not like anything else.

25:27.609 --> 25:33.605
It keeps me sharp. Makes me strong.
It's medicine.

25:34.116 --> 25:37.984
-|'m a better man on V.
-That's junkie talk, Andy.

25:38.412 --> 25:40.027
I'll give you a chance to prove it.

25:45.586 --> 25:48.703
Don't see something you like,
I got the bows and arrows over there.

25:48.881 --> 25:50.837
You crazy fucker.

25:51.008 --> 25:54.216
-What's this got to do with me?
-Choose your weapon.

25:54.386 --> 25:55.887
We'll see who's the better man.

25:58.474 --> 25:59.589
This shit is ridiculous.

25:59.767 --> 26:04.636
Vampires are gonna bomb Shreveport?
They can't glamour the whole fucking city.

26:04.813 --> 26:07.475
Yeah, they can.
It's what they did at the hotel.

26:07.941 --> 26:09.977
We're the only humans
who know what went on.

26:10.152 --> 26:12.313
-Well, can't the police do anything?
JASON: Like what?

26:12.488 --> 26:14.900
Put up yellow tape? Direct traffic?

26:15.074 --> 26:18.066
Even a SWAT team's no good
against magic.

26:18.243 --> 26:22.327
Besides, those Shreveport boys ain't
gonna believe a Bon Temps deputy...

26:22.498 --> 26:24.784
...or an anonymous tip,
which we already tried...

26:24.958 --> 26:26.914
-...and I got laughed off the phone.
LAFAYETTE: Tara.

26:27.086 --> 26:29.919
TARA [ON VOICEMAIL]: It's Tara, talk to me.
-Voicemail. Fuck Marnie.

26:30.089 --> 26:32.831
Don't blame her. She wouldn't
have anything to do with this.

26:33.008 --> 26:35.670
Marnie's a victim. She's trapped.

26:35.844 --> 26:37.755
-|t's the Spanish spirit.
-Whatever.

26:37.930 --> 26:40.421
If she would have
let her parakeet rest in peace...

26:40.599 --> 26:44.183
...then Eric Northman and Bill Compton
wouldn't be marching on Moongoddess...

26:44.353 --> 26:47.390
...to blow up my only fucking cousin.

26:52.486 --> 26:54.818
Look, I know Marnie better
than anyone else.

26:54.988 --> 26:57.650
lfl can reach her,
she'll help us push Antonia out...

26:57.825 --> 27:00.032
...and send her back to
wherever she came from.

27:02.621 --> 27:04.407
It's the only way.

27:05.958 --> 27:09.701
That's Latin, Holly. I don't speak Latin.
Do you?

27:09.878 --> 27:12.915
Yeah, I speak Latin. I need it for my job.

27:13.090 --> 27:15.547
No, I don't.
We're just gonna just have to wing it.

27:16.260 --> 27:18.546
Yeah, but what if we pronounce
something wrong...

27:18.720 --> 27:23.180
...and instead of breaking her spell,
we start a plague of locusts in here?

27:23.725 --> 27:25.465
Not gonna lie.

27:25.894 --> 27:28.761
-|t's a possibility.
-Great. Love it.

27:29.356 --> 27:35.898
See, magic is about energy and intention,
and I'm thinking...

27:36.071 --> 27:39.279
...maybe the goddess will know
what we mean, even if we say it wrong.

27:39.449 --> 27:41.906
Well, that's a big fucking maybe.

27:42.077 --> 27:45.240
Your attitude is not helpful.
What we need here is some faith.

27:45.414 --> 27:47.655
Well, that's not really my thing.

27:48.750 --> 27:52.117
You burnt the shit out of your hand
on a fucking doorknob.

27:52.296 --> 27:55.959
There's a 400-year—old witch
and two zombie vampires in the bathroom.

27:56.133 --> 27:58.590
You're telling me you don't have faith
in magic?

27:58.760 --> 28:00.887
It's all around you.

28:01.180 --> 28:03.045
Yeah, but....

28:03.223 --> 28:06.681
Believe in us, Tara.

28:07.102 --> 28:08.763
Believe in yourself.

28:08.937 --> 28:14.853
Believe that there's something out there
that's bigger than us and it's on our side.

28:16.111 --> 28:17.897
Can you do that?

28:22.701 --> 28:24.862
[GRUNTING]

28:27.039 --> 28:28.950
ANTONIA:
I am leaving you.

28:30.792 --> 28:33.283
What do you mean?
We haven't finished our work.

28:33.462 --> 28:36.795
-We've barely begun.
-I cannot go on, not after last night.

28:36.965 --> 28:40.457
Last night was a victory.
We almost assassinated the king.

28:40.636 --> 28:44.470
One king of one state Of one country.

28:44.640 --> 28:48.303
In my time, it was different.
Your world is huge.

28:48.477 --> 28:52.345
It is teeming with these creatures.
And what about the humans?

28:52.522 --> 28:57.767
All that blood and panic
and the screaming...

28:57.945 --> 29:01.403
lt sickens me.
We are no better than our enemies.

29:01.573 --> 29:03.404
Of course we are.

29:03.575 --> 29:06.157
No, we don't torture and kill.
We fight people who do.

29:06.328 --> 29:08.740
-This is not who I am.
-But it is.

29:08.914 --> 29:12.702
You are a fighter.
You are a great necromancer.

29:12.876 --> 29:17.165
| only turned to necromancy
to control death...

29:17.339 --> 29:20.001
...to save my village from fever.

29:21.051 --> 29:22.757
l was a healer.

29:22.928 --> 29:25.135
I saved lives.

29:26.223 --> 29:29.511
I delivered babies with these hands.

29:30.185 --> 29:33.177
I did not come back
to shed the blood of the innocent.

29:33.355 --> 29:34.845
But they are not innocent.

29:36.024 --> 29:38.356
They are sympathizers.

29:40.404 --> 29:43.020
They are collaborators.

29:44.533 --> 29:47.616
-You hate them.
-No, not everybody.

29:47.869 --> 29:49.860
But you have been gone
a long time, Antonia.

29:50.038 --> 29:52.529
I don't think you remember
what people are really like.

29:52.708 --> 29:56.917
They are cruel, they are bullies,
they treat you like a pariah.

29:57.087 --> 30:01.296
They are just, you know,
mocking and judging and shunning me...

30:01.466 --> 30:04.173
...when I didn't ask to be what I am.

30:04.928 --> 30:06.714
They did the same to me.

30:06.888 --> 30:09.379
Those people who you healed...

30:09.558 --> 30:14.552
...they watched you burn,
and they did nothing.

30:14.730 --> 30:17.096
Have you forgotten that?

30:17.274 --> 30:18.309
No.

30:18.483 --> 30:21.896
And they watched your agony
like it was sport.

30:22.070 --> 30:25.278
They smelled your flesh roasting,
and they did nothing--

30:25.449 --> 30:27.735
-They couldn't.
-They wouldn't.

30:27.909 --> 30:30.776
They thought of nothing but themselves.

30:31.872 --> 30:34.079
But you and l....

30:36.251 --> 30:39.789
There is a communion of souls.

30:39.963 --> 30:42.170
I know you feel it too.

30:42.674 --> 30:45.131
I know how lonely you've been
through the centuries...

30:45.302 --> 30:48.760
...wandering, aching for an end
Of your exile.

30:49.431 --> 30:51.046
Yes.

30:51.224 --> 30:55.593
Fate brought us together to fight evil.

30:58.023 --> 31:00.605
Did you really think
no one was gonna get hurt?

31:01.610 --> 31:03.100
No.

31:05.072 --> 31:07.279
Don't abandon us.

31:07.908 --> 31:09.193
We need you.

31:09.368 --> 31:14.658
-For a life without vampires.
-Yes.

31:17.292 --> 31:18.657
My sister.

31:26.009 --> 31:28.045
[GROANS]

31:33.350 --> 31:36.638
You'll ruin everything we've worked for
all these years.

31:36.812 --> 31:40.179
When I get out of here at dark,
your goddamn goose is cooked.

31:40.357 --> 31:44.646
Painful, degrading execution,
that's what's in store for you, Bill.

31:44.945 --> 31:47.903
Uh-huh. And what's the biggest
thermobaric payload?

31:48.365 --> 31:51.357
-We'll take two.
-Don't listen to her.

31:51.535 --> 31:54.652
She doesn't know it yet,
but it's the end of her time.

31:55.038 --> 31:57.825
What the fuck do you know?
True death for you too, Northman.

31:57.999 --> 31:59.990
Don't threaten him,
you incompetent bitch.

32:00.168 --> 32:01.499
Fuck you. Ugh.

32:01.670 --> 32:02.705
True death for you too.

32:02.879 --> 32:05.541
I don't care what happens
as long as | get to kill shit.

32:05.715 --> 32:07.046
The price is irrelevant.

32:07.217 --> 32:09.879
If everything is ready to go by sundown.

32:10.345 --> 32:13.553
JASON: Don't know about you guys,
but this place gives me the creeps.

32:13.723 --> 32:15.133
And where is everybody?

32:15.308 --> 32:17.435
| feel some bad juju.

32:17.602 --> 32:19.979
Antonia cleared out
the whole neighborhood?

32:20.147 --> 32:21.853
It's a repelling spell.

32:22.023 --> 32:24.230
Oh. Glad to know
I'm not just chickenshit.

32:24.401 --> 32:26.187
-Hey, who's in there?
-Bunch of people.

32:26.361 --> 32:28.693
-Hard to tell them apart.
-Find Tara.

32:28.864 --> 32:30.604
She'll be the loudest.

32:30.949 --> 32:32.985
[VOICE CHATTERING INDISTINCTLY]

32:34.077 --> 32:36.910
TARA: Drag her in a cage
and beat her ass good.

32:37.080 --> 32:39.537
She's there, and she's mad.

32:39.708 --> 32:42.825
-Pissed off, like usual. That's a good sign.
-You guys wish me luck.

32:43.003 --> 32:44.038
Wait.

32:45.839 --> 32:46.874
What?

32:47.048 --> 32:49.209
Are you really gonna try to do
the Mavis move?

32:49.384 --> 32:50.885
In principle.

32:51.052 --> 32:53.304
Antonia doesn't sound lost or confused...

32:53.472 --> 32:55.884
...and she sure doesn't look like
she wants to leave.

32:56.057 --> 32:59.675
But I gotta save Marnie,
and I'm irresistible, right?

32:59.853 --> 33:03.391
I don't like it. You're walking
into the mystical un-fucking-known.

33:03.565 --> 33:07.808
This isn't my first time
or my second time, and it won't be my last.

33:07.986 --> 33:10.693
-That don't make it right.
-All right, guys. You know what?

33:10.864 --> 33:11.979
-|'|| go.
-No, Jason.

33:12.157 --> 33:15.741
Why not? I'm the law.
And I can lie. I can fight.

33:15.911 --> 33:18.903
-I can run like the fucking wind.
-But you aren't magic.

33:19.080 --> 33:20.991
JESUS: Everything will be okay.
-Hey.

33:21.583 --> 33:23.448
-See you soon.
-Yeah.

33:24.753 --> 33:26.914
-Sookie, listen for me.
-I will.

33:27.088 --> 33:28.669
-Careful, man.
-Cuidate, baby.

33:38.308 --> 33:39.388
JESUS: Ah!
-Oh, shit.

33:39.559 --> 33:41.095
-Fuck.
-What's going on?

33:43.313 --> 33:44.598
SOOKIE:
Hey.

33:46.483 --> 33:47.939
Wait, wait.

33:49.653 --> 33:50.688
HOLLY:
Jesus.

33:50.862 --> 33:54.104
Lafayette wouldn't have
let him come alone. Reinforcements.

33:54.282 --> 33:55.442
[CLATTERING]

34:00.455 --> 34:01.911
[MARNIE SPEAKS IN LATIN]

34:03.124 --> 34:04.660
SOOKIE:
Get down.

34:07.295 --> 34:08.671
Hey, she walked out.

34:08.838 --> 34:10.965
-She didn't get burnt.
-Get out my way.

34:11.132 --> 34:12.633
-No.No.
-You idiots, no.

34:12.801 --> 34:14.291
[TREVOR & CASEY SCREAM]

34:14.469 --> 34:16.380
This is incredible.

34:17.138 --> 34:18.639
[GROANS]

34:20.809 --> 34:22.720
What power.

34:24.062 --> 34:28.396
-|t's a simple protection spell.
-Marnie?

34:28.567 --> 34:30.808
-Antonia.
-My name is--

34:30.986 --> 34:35.980
I know who you are.
Marnie and | share everything.

34:36.157 --> 34:38.193
-Then you know I'm her friend.
-Are you?

34:38.368 --> 34:41.701
Where have you been? We needed you.

34:41.871 --> 34:43.077
Mexico.

34:43.832 --> 34:46.539
It was an emergency.
My grandfather's very sick.

34:46.710 --> 34:49.543
I'm so sorry.
I should have told you before I left...

34:49.713 --> 34:52.500
-...but I came back as soon as I could.
-Marnie trusts you.

34:52.674 --> 34:56.792
-We trust each other.
-|'m a little harder to convince.

34:56.970 --> 34:58.255
Tell me what I have to do.

34:59.014 --> 35:00.345
Come to me.

35:01.683 --> 35:02.718
Through the wall?

35:04.644 --> 35:08.182
-Antonia.
-We have enough weak links in our circle.

35:08.356 --> 35:10.312
If you can't do it...

35:10.483 --> 35:13.145
...l have no use for you.

35:17.240 --> 35:18.776
-Can he do it?
-Calling this Off.

35:18.950 --> 35:20.736
Hey. Get down.

35:21.870 --> 35:24.361
[JESUS GROANING]

35:37.052 --> 35:38.758
Fuck. Fuck.

35:38.928 --> 35:41.590
He wants to keep trying. I can hear him.

35:50.357 --> 35:52.348
[SCREAMS]

35:53.234 --> 35:55.486
What the fuck's happening with his head?

35:56.071 --> 35:58.938
It's a Latin thing.

36:10.460 --> 36:11.495
Ah.

36:17.759 --> 36:19.169
Welcome back.

36:25.809 --> 36:27.765
Why don't you know
where your Old man's at?

36:27.936 --> 36:31.178
I mean, he's the type to check in
every five minutes.

36:31.356 --> 36:33.768
Mm. Once upon a time.

36:34.693 --> 36:37.776
He didn't come home last night,
and I ain't heard from him all day.

36:37.946 --> 36:39.607
It's how he treats me now.

36:39.781 --> 36:40.861
[THE KILLS' "SUPERSTITION" PLAYS]

36:41.032 --> 36:42.533
I'd tell you if I knew.

36:43.618 --> 36:45.449
Well, I appreciate that.

36:45.620 --> 36:48.077
What do you want him for?

36:48.957 --> 36:50.868
We're in the need of a frank discussion.

36:52.877 --> 36:56.711
-You don't like him.
-Different philosophies.

36:56.881 --> 36:59.167
Him and me,
we've got the same problem.

36:59.926 --> 37:01.587
Really?

37:01.761 --> 37:05.800
Yeah, ljust wanna be normal,
you know, run with my pack...

37:05.974 --> 37:07.635
.uhunt”

37:07.809 --> 37:10.016
...have kids.

37:10.186 --> 37:13.303
Alcide likes it on his own, as you know.

37:13.982 --> 37:16.223
He doesn't want kids.

37:18.319 --> 37:20.696
Well, that don't make sense.

37:21.823 --> 37:25.816
I mean, my little girl,
she makes life worth living.

37:29.414 --> 37:31.370
Yeah, I'd give anything for a baby.

37:31.541 --> 37:34.078
He says it's too hard
to be a wolf these days.

37:34.252 --> 37:36.163
He doesn't want to put
a child through it.

37:36.337 --> 37:37.873
[LAUGHS]

37:38.047 --> 37:39.583
[SIGHS]

37:40.341 --> 37:42.332
-What total bullshit.

37:42.510 --> 37:44.125
[LAUGHS]

37:46.097 --> 37:48.713
That's funny. That's what I said.

37:51.644 --> 37:55.353
-I don't know what to do about it.
-Sure you do.

37:58.109 --> 38:01.522
You hook up with a different wolf.

38:03.448 --> 38:05.860
I'm just about ready.

38:07.702 --> 38:08.942
[TIRES SCREECHING]

38:15.668 --> 38:18.910
SAM: Marcus!
NATE: He ain't here.

38:19.088 --> 38:21.625
[EL CAMINO'S "LAWD HAVE MERCY"
PLAYS ON RADIO]

38:22.425 --> 38:24.711
If you're lying,
l'll shoot you between the eyes.

38:24.886 --> 38:27.343
It's the truth. Now get out
before somebody gets hurt.

38:27.514 --> 38:30.551
-Somebody did get hurt.
-Alcide, you got your wires crossed.

38:30.725 --> 38:33.216
-We're pack.
-Somebody got killed.

38:33.394 --> 38:36.477
-I don't know.
-Somebody got beat to death. Four on one.

38:36.648 --> 38:38.980
And you're one of the fucking four.

38:39.442 --> 38:40.978
-You murdered my brother.
-Christ.

38:41.152 --> 38:42.938
For what? For what?

38:43.112 --> 38:44.568
We weren't trying to murder him.

38:44.739 --> 38:47.606
We were just kicking the shit out Of him.
Don't let him shoot.

38:47.784 --> 38:51.652
-I told you to stop. You wouldn't listen.
-Marcus is the one I really want.

38:51.830 --> 38:54.321
Right now, I'll settle for you.

38:54.499 --> 38:55.989
[GRUNTING]

39:08.137 --> 39:09.843
[GROANS]

39:10.014 --> 39:11.424
-Good shot.
-Shut the fuck up.

39:11.599 --> 39:14.136
-Want the AK?
-I don't need a AK to hit a paint can.

39:14.310 --> 39:16.767
Looks like you do. Reload.

39:22.360 --> 39:25.477
This don't prove nothing.
I ain't been to the range in a while.

39:25.655 --> 39:27.441
That's all.

39:29.784 --> 39:30.944
Are we done? Can we go?

39:31.119 --> 39:32.484
-Nope.
-What do you want?

39:32.662 --> 39:34.618
Admit you're a fucking drug addict.

39:34.789 --> 39:38.281
You want to humiliate me.
You always did.

39:39.711 --> 39:42.373
-Ugh.
-BuHshH.

39:42.547 --> 39:44.128
l was the humiliated one.

39:44.299 --> 39:47.632
Bullshit. The second you were born,
I fell off the face of the earth.

39:47.802 --> 39:50.965
-I don't remember it that way.
-You were a baby, stupid.

39:51.139 --> 39:53.380
Don't call me stupid.

39:57.478 --> 40:01.312
Everybody in the family's like, "Look at
little Terry. He's so cute, he's so sweet."

40:01.482 --> 40:04.645
My mama knit you booties
when she should have been knitting for me.

40:04.819 --> 40:07.982
-You were too old for booties.
-I wasn't too old for socks.

40:08.156 --> 40:10.488
She could have knitted me socks
or a sweater.

40:13.661 --> 40:14.821
That ain't the way it was.

40:14.996 --> 40:18.329
Then you got bigger, and they were like,
"Terry, he's so good-looking.

40:18.499 --> 40:19.784
He's a track star.

40:19.959 --> 40:23.247
